element_texts.text: Completed
brown journal cover, no text, latched by loop and tab method
Completed

Monday. Feb.10.1862- Washing.
Mending stair carpet. Wilder not
well - at home all day-
Tuesday Feb 11- Snowy.  Anna up here
in P.M. Put down stair carpet in
P.M. Wilder at home
Wednesday Feb 12-Fair.
Soc. Mrs. Cooly  [?] did not go. Mending Isaac's
coat etc. - Mrs E. Higby at Dr's. Wilder
to school again.
Thursday. Feb 13. Mending in AM
Mary & I to Anna's to spend P.M.
To meeting in evening - Letter from
Father. (Mr. Hoyle funeral at 2 o'clock)
Completed

Friday, February 14 – fair.
Wrote to Susan B and to Frank P.
Mended May's dress etc.
Wrote Valentine for Wilder to E. unclear –
Mrs.. Mussey and Flora in PM.
Gertrude Exchange letters with 
Jenny – brought me one from father 
and one from H. D. Newcomb.
Saturday February 15 – Fair and cold
Sweeping in AM.  Mrs. Laundon called
50 c. for soldiers Aid Society. Jenny and baby
all day.  Herbert to dinner and supper.
Mother and little Charley to Drs.  Isaac
to Dr. Montens to meeting in evening
Completed

Sunday February 16 –
Went to church and I.S. and to evening 
meeting – unclear
(class Miss Gilbert)
Monday February 17 -
Called at Anna's and Miss Florry
and to store.  bought 4 1/2 yards
nankinett for my skirt and 
a piece of yellow flannel -
$1.69 - Mrs Simons on way home.
Tuesday February 18 - fair
Invited to Mrs Simons just 
ready to go when Hale and Jenny

came. Delayed till evening.
Completed

Wednesday February 19 - Stormy
Dr. and Anna to Halter and Mrs.
Higbee & baby in PM.  Isaac
took home in sleigh - great
snow storm.
Thursday February 20 - Fine 
Most snow of season.
Sewing and etc.  Issac to woods in 
AM and down town in AM
I home all day – not to meeting in evening –
Friday February 21 Fine 
Good sleighing.  Invitation to Dr.
Manten's to tea with Dr. DeMitts
people.  Isaac, mother and I went.
Letter from Augusta W.
Completed

Saturday February 22
Washington's Birthday -
Wilber and Charlie to Lirrn Row's
Birth Day party - Anna in AM
Isaac and I to ride with Anna
in P.M.  Called at W. Nibins
and at Jennys to read George
letter - To meeting in evening
Sabbath February 23
"Father Keep" 'This is the victory
that overcometh the world even
our faith" P.M.
S. I. at noon heard class
Monday February 24
Wrote to father - verse "Heart and Home"
Sewing on chemise
Completed

Tuesday February 25
Writing George - Aunt Frances and E. Paddoch
Anna to dinner.  Mrs. Mussey come in
PM.  Mrs. Nelson too.
Scrapbook in Evening. Mr. Wilbur and
Mr. Cobb called.
Wednesday, February 26.
Went into Mrs. Simons and Mrs. Hamilton
in P.M.  Letter form Aunt Frances 
and cousin Frances
Thursday February 27
To meeting at Eleven.  Dianna and Dr. 
Amhotylae [?].  Mr. Wilbur's and Doolittle
and Chittendens.
Completed

Friday February 28 - Cold _est ?
Meeting at half past two -
[?]to Woolents for Braid [?] and for
Worsted.  Jenny's
with aunt and cousin Frances' letter.
Saturday March 1 - 1862
Sweeping and making paper
holders in AM.  Charlie and
Wilder and Isaac and self to Drs.
to supper.  Mother M's birth
day - 75 [95?] years.  Mr. Cobb Bible
agent to spend Sabbath
Sabbath March 2
Mr. Wilbur - 1 Pet. 2 = 4, 5, 9 -
Communion in PM.  Concern in evening
Isaac alone to concert.  Mr. Cobb still 
here.
Completed

Monday March 3 - Mr. Cobb here
Rain - Herbert home.
Brought note from Irma for Aunt F.
Tuesday March 4
Wrote to Aunt Frances Putnam
(Paper holders for letters.)
Mr. Cobb still here.
Wednesday March 5 - 
went out in PM.  Called for WIlder 
and went into Anna's and Mrs. Finns
Mr. Cobb left after supper.
Thursday March 6 -
To meeting in evening with Isaac.
Completed

Friday March 7
Invited to supper to Mrs.
Toplifts - Mrs.Wilbur, Redfield,
Boggswell, Pond and Mussey - 
Went with Libby and Charles and
(May about eleven) to Miss Brandals
school and home.  Mrs. Toplifts 
to supper.
Saturday March 8 -
Wilder and Charles to see Eddie Cary
Sabbath March 9
I went to church in AM and to SS.
Teach -"Seek ye first the Kingdom 
of Heaven etc.
Completed

Monday March 10 - rain
Isaac sick with cold
Wrote to father
Tuesday March 11 - washing
Went to Anna's a moment 
and to see [dress ?] maker. Mrs.
Wildon could not do any work 
Mrs. Chittenshins not at home
(note to Mrs. Baker)
Wednesday March 12
Anna here in the AM Wrote to
Almeides.  Went in P.M. to
Mrs. Strong's to society (37)
Completed

Thursday March 13 - 
Fine - To meeting in Evening alone
Isaac cold some better
Friday March 14
To Anna's to sew in PM and to
meeting Mr. and Mrs. Wilbur
Letter from Miss Newcomb 
and Mrs. Barston.  Herbert home -
Invited to Mrs. Hamilton's - not go.
Saturday March 15 -
About sick with cold and toothache
Dr. in Evening - just home from west.
Sabbath March 16 -
Not out at all - face swelled
Headache
Completed

Monday March 17 - 
Mother come home
Herbert home.  On lounge all
day windy -
Tuesday March 18
Herbert and Jimmy in AM
Wednesday March 19 - 
Anna to dinner.  Knitting etc.
Gingham dress making over (better
Soc. Mrs. Cranes
Thursday March 20
Face better.  Gingham dress.
Invitation to Mr. Strong's for evening
rain hard.  not go. Letter to father.
Completed

Friday March 21 =
Saturday March 22
Sabbath March 23. Snowy -
Did not go out.
Monday March 24
Tuesday March 25
Anna here in A.M. to Dinner
Libby and Mary in Evening
I went into Mrs. Mussey in AM
and visited Mrs. Hamilton in PM
Dr. and Mrs Colten, Mr. and Mrs Hayhunst, 
Mr. Leonard, Mrs. Redfield, Toplift, Moone Brown
Completed

Thursday March 27

Went downtown in to Buldinns

and bought print for dress etc. -
Mr. Tilton to dine and Felten and Cobb
to supper.  Into school - grammar
and secondary in PM.
(Wednesday - 26 - Walter and Emma
Brown to spend P.M.)
Friday March 28 -
Miss Wilson to dress maker
Misses Felten and Cobb both home.
Went to High school all day - 
Mrs. Cole and Miss Evans called
Mrs. Felten left
Saturday 29 March - rain
Mr. Cobb left.  Miss Wilson here.
Completed

Sabbath 30 March
To Meeting in A M
Sabbath School at noon.  9 pupils
To meeting in evening
Monday 31 March - Fair
Washing - Herbert (parsnips and 
salsify) - Talk of unclear
Tuesday April 1 - Fair
Sewing - May out with boys
Mr. Elliot of Rochester here to
dinner His mother a Putnam of 
Sutton Mass.
Completed

Thursday April 3 -
Over to Jennny's with May in AM
Anna and Dr. here to supper.
Did not go to meeting in Evening
Friday April 4 Church meeting in P.M.
Mrs. Hall & Dr. DeMitt
Saturday April 5  Mr. Gilton to Bible
meeting in PM and back to Oberlin
I went to Bible meeting P.M.
Isaac's secretary's Report etc.
Called on Jenny - saw Mr. and Mrs.
Brooks the grandparents
Completed

Sabbath April 6 -
To Meeting in AM.  Mother in 
PM. to [?] concert.  Mrs. Lilten
to supper and spend night.  I went
to Anniversary Bible Meeting in 
Evening.  Full house.
Monday April 7 -
Home all day.
Tuesday April 8 - Rain cold
Hattie here to supper
Wednesday April 9 Rain
Dr. White and Mother's [unclear]
Anna up here in AM.  Libby too.
Completed

Thursday April 10
I went down to Anna's - sewed
some - downtown - look at
bonnets.  To meeting in evening
Miss Lane buried.
Friday April 11 -
Mrs and Mrs. Wilbur and  Dr. to Anna's
Mrs Crane, Mrs. Book to supper
Saturday April 12
Downtown with all the children 
in AM.  Stanns for silk bonnet 4.50
In Baldwin's Bill for goods 2.12
Sewing at Anna's till noon.
Mother to Mrs. Mussey's - Henny Brooks 
over in P.M. with Sofia.
Completed

Sabbath April 13 - 
Mr. Wilbur Not by might nor by power and c
I went to meeting and I. S. and to
Lecture in evening.
Monday April 14 -
Making soup.  Mrs. Grandall, 
Montieth, Mussey and Crane
to supper.
Tuesday 15 - Fair
Home all day - Anna here
Wednesday 16 - Fair
Thursday 17 - Rain
Did not go to meeting in evening
Friday 18 - Cleaning up
Stairs, Home all day
Saturday 19 At Dr. DeMitts to
tea - Mrs. Monteith, Gates, Snow and
Finn.
Completed

Sabbath 20 April
Went to church in AM and to 
S. S. and to Evening Lecture with
Charlie Rich.  Isaac lame
back at home
Monday 21 - Rain-
Tuesday 22 - Rain in AM
Wednesday 23 - Cleaning
house at home.
Thursday 24.
Went to meeting in Evening
Called at Dr. Parasol 2.20
Friday 25.
New carpet bottoms to  three
chairs in AM.  To ride
in P.M. (Cemetery).
Cleaned Mother's room.
Completed

Saturday 26.
Sweeping [unclear] out of doors
a good deal - changing Earth 
in flower pots.  Gertrude home
Sabbath 27 - Did not go to 
church. in AM. went in evening
Monday 28 - Rain
Tuesday 29 - Anna here
Wednesday 30 Cleaning shelves in 
closet. Writing some. Ironing
cleaning my closet drawers
and shelves - Anna here
Thursday May 1 - cleaning my room
Little May 3 years old.
Went down with Grandma
to Anna's - Hattie came
home with them.
Completed

Friday May 2 - letter geroge
Cleaning in Dining Room 
and finishing in bedroom
Saturday May 3.
Resting.
Sabbath May 4. To church in AM.
and two communion in P. M.
Monday May t - sweeping etc.
Little May Sun Bonnet - in AM
In P.M.  delightful ride to Charlie's
Mr. Dascombs. Mary's letters and
D ca. Parkins letter - (Kate Moran).
Tuesday May 6 -
To father and Miss Newcomb.  Anna here.
I went down town in PM with Anna
Baldwin's - $4.00 - stockings at Woolcuts
Completed

Wednesday - May 7 -
Cleaning Dressing Room.  Book case
and closet drawers in AM
In P.M. went down town - into
Anna's - Griswolds book 22
Baldwin's Hats 1.25
Called on Mrs. Judy Ely and Mrs.
Arthur Ely, Mrs. Boyd, Jenny
and Mr. Hale.
Thursday May 8
With May into Mrs. Toplifts and
Mussey's.  To meeting in Evening
Left May's hat at Miss Runes
and Got Gertrude's dress. 2.86
Completed

Friday, May 9 -
Cut up and arranged old dinning
room carpet in AM.  Isaac 
took Mother and I to meeting at
Mrs. H. E. Brooks at three o'clock.
(Mrs. George Ely and Mrs. Rond) Sat an
hour with Mrs. B. after meeting.
Saturday, May 10
Working nearly all day, over 
old carpet. Two pieces for
bedroom one for front 
chamber - Hattie called.
Sabbath, May 11 - fine-
To church in AM Genesis 16.13 -
and to evening Lecture.  Very beautiful
evening.  Fruit trees by moonlight
as if covered with snow flakes.
Completed

Monday May 12 -
Anna here in AM.  I was
mending.  After dinner I went 
down - sewed on May's apron
Isaac's neckerchiefs etc.
Mrs. Hall and Jenny to tea.
Down town - Toothbrush at
Woolcut's paid for 13 cents
Hoop skirt at Stann's 1.75
Miss Runes about May's hat
[unclear] old barn.
Completed

Tuesday May 13 -
Isaac with Anna to [?]
S.I. Convention.  Sweeping etc.
Cut asparagus and prepared 
for market and sent little boys 
with it.  Corey moving barn-
finishing.  Rain in P.M.
Isaac home at night.
Wednesday May 14.
Sewing etc. Wilder over to Jenny's.
Jenny over here for the after noon.
Home at half past five - Mrs. Pudy and
Mrs. Johnson called.  Letter from 
Aunt Frances B and from father.
Cut jackets and pants for boys
Gertrude cleaning in pantry.
Completed

Thursday May 15 - Fine
Asparagus down town.
Cleaning in wood shed etc.
Dr. Cushing and Halter in PM.
Hattie to supper - went to
meeting in evening.  Mr. Tilton
to supper and all night etc.
Friday, May 16 - Fine -
Dr. and Anna home - up here
in P.M. Sewing - Hats for boys
in P.M. lined and bound.  Down
town to Anna's after tea.
Saturday May 17-
Thirty-three years old to
day.  O that I were wiser and
better.
Completed

Sabbath May 18 - 
To meeting and I.S. and to evening
lecture.  Bethel man 
preached in AM
Monday May 19 -
Isaac took Dr. DeMitt
to Grafton in morning
and Mother down to Anna's 
on returning.  Mending 
and sewing.
Completed

Tuesday May 20
Down town.
Bill at Baldwins $3.57
Sewing and Anna's till after dinner.
Wednesday May 21
Wrote to father
Rain most of day
Did not go to Society at
Mr. A. Beekin's Inn.
Thursday May 22
Fine.  Sowing flower seeds
Charley's pants made.
Went to evening meeting.
Completed

Friday May 23.
Letter from father .
Boy's jackets in A.M. Called
on Mrs Hill.  Worked in garden
Saturday, May 24.
Out in garden most of the AM.
Anna here in P.M.  Flora Kellogg
called.  Isaac, Anna and I to
ride.
Sabbath May 25.
To meeting and IS and
evening lecture.  Read "Primitive
Piety Revived".
Completed

Monday May 26 - 
(Fine) Sweeping etc.
Ride after supper.  Call Jenny's.
Tuesday May 27
White washing etc.
Garden in AM
Wednesday May 28
White wash dining room
Mary Hamilton two hours and
Herbert B.  Down to Dr's night.
Thursday May 29
Sewing etc.  Call with May at
Mrs. Pond's.  Meeting in Evening
Call at Mrs. Jenkins.
Completed

Friday May 30 - Rain
To meeting in P.M. and into Baldwins
with Anna after. Ribbon to trim
May's cape and borage for mother's
shaker.  28 cents.  Called at 
Wilbur's.  Anna home with me
over to Biggs house where Isaac is papering
Saturday May 31 - Rain
Mending.  Making cape for May and 
Anna up at night.  Mary Doolittle here 
an hour (Trimming paper Bigg's house)
June Sabbath June 1-
To meeting in AM and to hear Mr. 
Stockwell for the Howard Mission.
Completed

Monday, June 2 - Rain
Sweeping.  Finished May's cape
Anna in PM - Mrs. Topliff.
Tuesday June 3 - Rain
Papering in kitchen.
Finished the papering boxes for 
boys.  Anna here just at night.
Wednesday June 4 - Rain
Made carpet for dining room
Gertrude cleaned kitchen
[unclear] letter to Wilder
Wednesday, June 5.  Fair.
Got cold and feel bad.  Mending.
Pasting picture scrap book
Letter from Father.  Wrote Susie B.
Completed

Friday June 6 -
[unclear] bread (Graham).  Wrote Miss Woodbury
Saturday June 7-
Sabbath June 8
Gertrude home all day.  I went in AM and to I.S.
Monday June 9 - Fair
Washing.  I went in P. M. to 
Anna's and sewed.
Libbie at Baldwin's - Linen remnant .45

                               1 yard Brilliant .16
                                                      ––––  
                                                       .61
Completed

Tuesday June 10.
Picnic in Fair Grounds -  I chose
all of the schools. Anna up
here in PM.  Making pants.
Rode at night with two boys.
Wednesday June 11 - fair.
Gertrude when home.  not
well
Sabbath June 15.  Go to church once, S.S. class
Mother at home with May.
Mother and Isaac went at night.
Monday 16 - [unclear] most all day
about [unclear].  worked very
slowly.  Mrs. Mussey called
at night.  Hattie and F. Sanford
too about Soldier's Aid Festival.
Completed

Tuesday 17.  Baking. 
Strawberries.  Sweeping etc.
Mother helping as usual
[2 words unclear]. Anna at night
for few moments. 
Wednesday 18 - Rain - 
Preparing work for machine
mending pants etc.
Thursday 19
Not very well. Down to Anna's
sewing some.  Tired. Did
not go down town as I intended.
Called and left $6.00 for Festival
at Mr. Sandford's.
Completed

Friday June 20
Strawberry Soldier's Aid 
Festival P.M. and evening
Anna here in PM and I went with 
her into Grammar schools
Rode down town just as night
and bought  linen (47 cents) for Charles pants
and 10 yard cotton (1.40) for family use
and three spools cotton  (.16)
Saturday June 21 - 
Baking.  tired.  Eddie Casey
to ask wilder to go with him 
I let him go two hours
and then he went to sing at
Miss Crandall's.  Charlie
covered thickly with [?] rash.
Completed

Sabbath June 22
To church and SS in AM
Mother and Isaac in Evening
Monday June 23
Rain.  May with rash.
Cut and made lined pants for 
Charlie.  Isaac to school
meeting till after twelve in evening
(10 quarts strawberries just before
supper.)  Letter from client
desiring Isaac to go to Pems.
Completed

Tuesday June 24
Isaac shirt.  Mother to Drs. in 
PM.  Isaac took Libbie and Mary
Higbee out to Mr. Halls.  Mrs.
Coltin till half past nine in evening
( unclear M. Ice cream.)
Wednesday June 25
Isaac started 1/2 past six
With Charlie Rich for Grafton.
Mrs. Cullen sent for course of 
study,  Dr. C sent package
by Willie McLong.  Nettie Wheeler
came to invite us to evening
party on account Lieut. C
Parsons at Horan Sturry.
Mr. Wilbur called in PM
Letter Miss Woodbury.
Completed

Gertrude picked strawberries 
from Biggs bed for supper.
Called at Mr. Henson's and
Mr. Waldo's.
Invite to unclear Lucy Pond
and Augusta W.
Thursday June 26
Picked a few cherries.  Charles
and Gertrude did.  Gathered 
unclear for Charlie Rich to take to
school.  Made loaf delicate 
cake. Sewing shirt memory
Hattie came up Mrs. Peachy
spent the afternoon.  I went
to meeting in Evening.  Mr. Wilbur
home with me.
Completed

Friday June 27.
Pickled two jars of cherries.
Charlie hay and hoeing and picking
strawberries.
At 1/2 past unclear bees swarming
Mr. Waldo to help 
Anna and I went to High school
Hattie and Mary Higbee called.
Saturday June 28 - 
Bees swarmed and went away.
Boys hoeing corn.  Mr. Waldo's
bees swarmed and Charlie Rich
helped him.  Rain in PM.  Then our
(cut overhauls) Mary Hamilton for 
flowers for supper party with Mr. Leonard.
Completed

Sunday June 29 - Raining
Charlie Rich and Wilder to meeting in A.M.
Reading "Primitive Piety"
Monday June 30.  Fair
Gertrude washing.  Mrs. Mussey
here in A.M.  I washing flannels
etc.  Picked strawberries and some
cherries.  Wilder to Jenny 
with note and chemise to Anna
with note from Grandmother.
Anna and Libbie at night.
Bees swarmed again from the cask.
Eleven quarts strawberries to Fisher's.
Completed

Tuesday July 1 1862
Charlie picking cherries at
Dr.'s home at four P.M.
Then hoeing till chore time
Paid Mrs Crandall $2.50
being Charlie music lesson fee.
Canned a few cherries - 7
quarts.  Gertrude ironing
Emma Crane called
Mending variously.
Wrote Maria Argo
with mother's.
Isaac about 1/2 past 10 at
night walked from Grafton.
Completed

Wednesday July 2 - Fine.
Isaac came last night after we were all gone to bed
Tired but feeling pretty well.
Cherries - canned 15 quarts - 
Isaac picked one  unclear. I
Sent down town ($1.28).
Libbie spent the afternoon
Thursday July 3 - 
Gooseberry jelly.  5 bowls.
(four pounds juice.)  Gooseberry jam
in two jars.  and 1 glass bottle.
Completed

Friday July 4 -
Did not go away from house at all
Hattie and Chester Knowles
here just at night.
Saturday July 5.
Ten years today married.
(Psalm 103.)
Mother and Isaac and Charley and
May to ride before supper.
Isaac, Wilder and I after.
Mr. Barmen called and
Dr. Catlin while Isaac
gone to woods for horse
Preponator Lecture in PM.
Completed

Sabbath July 6-
Sabbath - Communion
Did not go out at all.
Mother went in P.M.
Very warm 96 degrees for hours
Monday July 7 - warm
Washing - raspberries
Eighteen quarts to Mr.s Finn
Eight quarts 
Sent on Saturday for 
Mr. Horr and Zanesville
Teacher.  Mrs. McIntyre
for wood.  Game her cherries.
Miss Pond called.  Mother to
Doctors at night.  I rode a little way.
Completed

Tuesday July 8 = warm
Mending -  little boy's down
to Aunt Anna's.
Wednesday July 9
Libbie came for May.  She went 
home with her.  Hattie up at
night for her nightgown.
Herbert and Jenny here at night.
(Canning cherries and raspberries)
Thursday July 10
Currant Jelly and Jam.
Misses Bunsell called.
Picking raspberries and night
Little May still gone.
Completed

Friday July 11
Pickling Cherries
Cut out pants for Charlie
I rode out to Carlisle with
Isaac in PM.  Called at 
Jenny's and supper at Drs.
Little May home with us.
Dr. Catlin in evening He and 
Mrs. Wilson called.
Saturday July 12
Little boys over to see how Henry 
Brooks was.  I rode to Drs.
in P.M., while Isaac went to
Mill.
Completed

Sabbath July 13.
Home all day.  Little May
and I and Gertrude.
Monday July 14
Rain in A. M. Drying our
clothes in P.M.
Mrs. Hamilton at night
with errand from Mrs. Howes
(Charlie's linen pants)
Thursday July 16 - Fair-
Sewing.  Mrs. Mussey in 
A.M.  Hattie in P.M.
Sermon in Evening.  Isaac went.
(Jenny's baby at eleven in Evening)
Completed

Wednesday July 16 - Rain in A. M.
Picking Raspberries
Canned some and broke two glasses.
Thursday July 17.  Fair
Washing bed spreads.
Made currant jelly, black currents 
and gooseberry jam.
Rode just at night down to Drs.  May
and Charlie there all day.
Mother here at night.
Isaac to meeting .  Mrs. Wilbur
and children came to call while gone
to ride.  Herbert here in A.M.
Completed

Friday July 18 -
Mending.  Mother here.
Picking Raspberries
Eddie Carey here.
Saturday 19
Rode at night.  caught
in shower with May and  Charlie.
Sabbath - July 19
Home all day.  Reading
Independent etc.
Monday July 20
Rain in A.M. but
got clothes dry.
Rode at night.
Completed

Tuesday July 22
Letter from Father.
Wednesday July 23
Isaac to lake with three 
boys.  Warm.  Gertrude
picking currants. Six quart
pail ten times full.
Mrs. Heyhouse called.
Thursday July 24
Picking peas with May -
Mrs. Baldwin called.
Rode to Jenny's and to Anna's
Mother home.  I to supper at 
Dr's (Ten gallon currant wine.)
Completed

Friday July 25
Squashes to Jenny.
unclear 2 words.  ice cream.  Anna here
Isaac for Mrs. Howes at night
Saturday July 26
(Little baby girl at half 
past six in the morning.)
Boys to Drs for the day.
Express box from 
Home Yarmouth at night.
Saturday August 2.
Charlie five years old yesterday.  
Mrs Converse
and Anna called with Dr.
Wrote a little to S. W. Y.
Completed

Sabbath. August 10.  Fine
Mrs. Howes to meeting in A.M.
Letters during the week past
from Father and from Lucy Pond
Thursday S.I. picnic to Vermillion
Friday Hattie and Libbie to Cleveland.
Monday August 11.
Washing and some ironing
Dr. and Mrs. Dascomb and Anna
to supper.
Tuesday August 12
Herbert called.  Jenny 
at the gate.  Did not come 
in.  Wrote some to father.
Completed

Wednesday August 13
To ride in A. M. a sort 
distance.  Mother down 
to Anna's.  Mrs. Waldo and
Mrs. Peachy called.
Mrs. Howes to Mrs. Toplift's
with vest to stitch.
Baby two weeks old last Saturday.
Thursday. August 14.
Rain.  Baptist SS. Picnic.
Saturday 16 Fair
Ride at night.
Baby three weeks old - 10 pounds.
Sabbath 17  August -
Home with May and baby in A. M.
(Chaplain Jones of 42 Reg.)
Completed

Monday 18 August
Pleasant.  Mrs. Howes and
washing in the A. M.  In P.M. went 
over to Mr. [unclear].  I went 
to ride at night.
Tuesday 19 August
Rode in A.M. Delightful.
Mrs. Hoes over to Mrs. Toplift
in A.m. Isaac took her to Mr.
Mills in P.M. to see Mrs. S. Stavv,
Saturday August 30 Baby six weeks -10 pounds
Rode a little.  Stopped at
Jenny's.  She and baby both
unwell.  Mrs. J. J. Brooks
came to [unclear]
Completed

Sabbath August  31
Home with May and baby.
Read Independent.
Isaac to Monthly Con.
and to Evening.
The eleventh Sabbath
that I have been at home
Monday September 1
Rains in P.M.
(Cutting sweet apples to dry.)
Tuesday September 2
Mr. Hale called
Completed

Wednesday  September 3 -
Libbie here in P.M.
In A. M. rode over to Jenny's an
hour.
Thursday September 4
Gathering Flowers seeds.
Emilie in P.M. Pickled 
pears that Anna sent.
Isaac here about noon.
Long talk about the war.
The Generals, etc.
Friday September 5.  Fine.
Isaac and Mother to meeting in
P.M.  Anna here to supper.
Cutting sour apple for drying.
Completed

Saturday September 6
Anna here  Mr. Parker called
(the new School Superintendent)
Sabbath, September 7
Communion.  11 weeks since 
I went to meeting.
Monday September 8
Mrs. DeWitt here.  Mrs. 
Henderson and baby, Carrie
Massey, and Flora and Mary
Doolittle.
(Wilder to Primary School)
Completed

Tuesday September 9.
Cutting peaches for drying
Mrs. Cooly called at night.
Wednesday September 10
Wilder seven  years old
Cutting peaches all day.
Libbie here for peaches.
Thursday September 11
Cutting peaches and canning.  8 quarts
Friday September 12 Rain in A.M.
Canning 10 quarts of peaches. 2 Pears.
Completed

Saturday September 13
Jenny and Herbert here.
Jenny and I up stairs with 
Boy that came from Yarmouth.
Rode little at night.  Called
moment at Drs.
Mother about sick.
Sabbath September 14
Twelve weeks since I was at 
church.
Baby seven weeks - 12 pounds
Monday September 15
Anna here
Completed

Wednesday September 17 
Libbie here in Morning.  Mr. M.
Ely arrived there last evening
Isaac went down tin A. M.  to
see him. Come about Eleven
for baby, May and Me.  Evening went
to dinner.  Home at five.
Thursday September 18.
Cutting apples.  Isaac to
State Fair and Cleveland
May and I gathered [unclear]
Wilder over to Jenny's.
Completed

Friday September 19 - 
Sweeping and dusting.
Mr. and Mrs. Ingersole from 
Cleveland to dinner.  I called
with her at Mrs. [unclear]
Beautiful baby.  11 pounds.
Saturday September 20
Canning and drying snow peaches etc.
Libbie here in P.M.
Letters from Miss Davis  [unclear] at
Oberlin from Northboro Mass.
Mrs. Waldo called.
Completed

Sabbath September 21 - Fair and warm
Thirteen weeks to day since I 
went to meeting.
Monday September 22.  Warm.
Drying peaches with out paring.
Tooth ache hard.  Mr. Cobb of
the Bible Society to spend the night.
Tuesday September 23 - Warm very.
Mr. Cobb had lunch and left 
about noon.  Tooth ache
News of the President's Proclamation
of Emancipation.
(Mrs. Patterson gave pair gaiters.)
Completed

Wednesday September 24.
Called at Mrs. Waldo's
awhile.  Gertrude kept baby.
Thursday September 25
Sweeping and Dusting.
Mrs. Hazel German woman
with one hand.  Gave her 
one of my dresses and some baby
clothes - skirt - double dress etc.
Mother came home.
Friday September 26 -
Jenny here with little Henry.
I rode a little way with
baby, May and Charlie.
Completed

Saturday September 27
Baby two months old.
Weighed 13 1/4 pounds.
Anna, Hattie, Libbie
here.  Jenny and little 
Henry again.
Sabbath September 28 -
I went to meeting in Evening.
Fourteen weeks since 
I went last.
Completed

Monday September 29 - 
Baby awake all A.M.
Cutting apples to day Mother
and I.  Mrs. Kellogg called.
Tuesday September 30
Anna here to dinner.
Mrs. Simons called.
Drying more apples.
Wednesday October 1
Drafting - Avon and Black River
Completed

Thursday October 2
Drafting still
Friday October 3
Drafting - From Elyria in P.M.
Eleven men - Isaac not one.
I called at Mrs. Mussey's
Went all over the house
-Anna and Libbie here in Evening
Saturday October 4
Libbie and Hattie
Canning peaches etc.
Sabbath October 5
I went in Evening to Monthly 
Concert. Jovah.
Completed

Monday, October 6 - Fair
Baby up most of the day
E. Sundford came for books
Anna, Irene - work on silk for
[unclear] to our two dresses
Isaac and I called on Mr .
and Miss Parker
Wednesday October 8 - 
Carrie Mussey with Blood
Peaches - Louise Conklin
for a place as [unldear] girl.
Completed

Thursday October 9 - rain
Anna here.  I cutting 
apples all day long.
Friday - October 10 Rain some
Anna - I not feeing well
Pain in the head and side.
Saturday October 11
In bed somewhat considerable
pain.
Sabbath October 12
Isaac and Mother to meeting
Gertrude with me and baby.
Completed

Monday October 13 - Fair
Gathering Grapes and
preparing them to sel
mending pants.
Tuesday October 14 0 Fair
Isaac down town all day -
it being election day.
Herbert home.  Isaac picking grapes
Wednesday October 15
Isaac started for Illinois in
P.M.  Carrie Mussey came
in at night. Told me of the
loss of Horace Harris' silver
by "a thief in the night".
Took my plants onto verandah.
Completed

Thursday October 16
Cold and dreary.  Charles R.
Greathouse one bushel peaches
for Mr. Hitchcock.  He sent
for them and the grapes.
Anna here in A.M.
Little Charlie went down
to pick up apples for Uncle
Dr. carried a peck peaches 
for Mrs. Wilbur to go with 
Anna's.
Friday October 17 Fine
Mrs. Washburn called.
Completed

Friday October 17
Mrs. O'Brien for an order.Hattie to spend the day.
Jennie and Henry in P.M.
Emilie Griswold called.
I made little scarf for May.
Mended some.
Shoes for little Charlie
at Bagswells - .75
Saturday October 18
Charles got fish at
Hitchcocks
Sabbath October 19 - Fine
Mrs. WIlbur to Synod
little boys to S.S.
Completed

Monday October 20
Butter at Hitchcock's
May not very well
cutting apples
Tuesday October 21.
Baby's hood
Jenny and Herbert & Henry
Herbert brought cradle.
baby slept all evening in it
Letter from Isaac from  [unclear]
I wrote to him to mail in the morning.
Wednesday October 22
Mailed letter to Isaac. Cleaning up
stair.
Completed

Thursday October 23
Cleaning up stairs boy's room
{Woman with two children 
to be helped on journey)
Emily to see Mr. Metcalf.
Mr. Waldo took sorghum
Wilder to P. O. in morning
and got fine letters.  Once from
Father, one from Isaac \\Bangor.  Dr. C and FMRS
Friday October 24 -
Another letter from Isaac 
mailed at Matton Isles
and kd
Anna here it dinner 
I called at Mrs. Mussey's with her.
Completed

Herbert  and Jenny and
little Henry here to call
-Got a fright about little
Charlie - could not
find him for some time
Saturday October 25
Sabbath October 26  Rain-
Boys not to church but to S. S.
Completed

Monday 27 October
Anna here in  P.M.
Mrs. Peterson, Mrs. Musssey's
nurse with Flora called
Mrs. Darling and Mrs. Wilburn
Mrs.Waldo took cask for
sorghum.
Tuesday 28 October
Cold, cloudy and wind
(Headache.) Fixing silk
dress and skirt
Completed

Wednesday October 29 -
Headache.  Gertrude cleaning
the parlor and hall.
I went in P M. down to 
Annie to Soldier Society - stayed
till after supper.
Letter Isaac and
from Sarah Parker Kimball
Thursday October 30 - 
Went in P.M. to call on Mrs. Hale. 
(Fannie Snow).  Did not see her
Called on Mrs. Hill. Anna here
also Mrs. Lottie DeWitt and 
Jennie and Henry.
Grapes Catawba.
Completed

Friday October 31.
Anne here little while.
Isaac came home.
Libbie here to supper
Herbert in the evening.
Saturday November 1
Herbert in evening.
Cutting little [unclear] Wilde
Sabbath November 2
I went to church in P.M. to communion.  
Tornado and rain
to come home in.
Monday November 3 - blowy
Gertrude went to [unclear]
to meeting.  left washing.
Completed

Tuesday November 4
Anna here to ask us to
tea with Mrs. Moody and Mrs.
and Mr. Nelson.  Mother went
in A.M. Isaac and I at six -
home at nine - baby with
Gertrude and Margaret.
Wednesday November 5 - 
Little luck in A.M. Grapes -
to funeral of Mr. H. M.
Goodrich in P.M.  Isaac to Dr's
after apples.  Rain at night.
Completed

Thursday November 6
Got in apples
Friday November 7
Herbert here. Gathering and
looking over our Catawba grapes.
Anna here.  May's dress
Saturday November 8 - snow
Making May's dress.  Plaid
Delaine.  Mother making
blue merino
Sabbath November 9 -
I went to meeting in A.M.
in evening - "Much required"
in A.M.  Excellent.
Gertrude to Sheffield to
meeting.
Completed

Monday November 10 -
Writing to father and to 
Augusta Webster.
Little on May's dress.
Anna here.  Mrs. Wright
to see Isaac.
Tuesday November 11 - fine.
Sweeping.  Isaac took down
the pipe.
Wednesday November 12
Isaac to come to meet the
Ladies Mrs. Clark, Goddard
and daughter.  Isaac, baby and I
went to dinner at Dr's.
Completed

Thursday November 13 -
Charle went down to Drs
with little May - she
home with Grandmother
after dinner.  I went 
down town. First time
in many months.  Looked
at bonnets and bought 
cloth for pants for Wilder 
and jacket Charles Rich and
handkerchiefs for Isaac.
Friday November 14
Anna and ladies up here to
spend day.  Hattie
to tea and evening.  Anna 
home before tea.
Completed

Saturday November 15 
Anna and ladies in P.M.
Dr. to tea.
Herbert B. in evening - [unclear]
for him to go to [unclear]
He will go Monday.
Sabbath November 15
Home all day.  Mother went
down to Drs after meeting.
Monday November 17 - Rain-
Charles R got jacket cut
Isaac down town to go to
cars with Mrs. CLark
Completed

Tuesday 18 November - Rain
Isaac to car with Mrs.
Goddard and daughter. Into
school etc.  May dress
and mending.  Mrs. Hazel.
Wednesday 19 November - Rain
Isaac into school again.
Mays dress.

Mr. Watson wife and children 
here a week.
Completed

January 1 1863
Maria and Elias come
December 19.  Have been here
two weeks tomorrow
night.  Dr and Anna and 
Maria  and Hattie here 
to dinner today and Lizzie
and Mary Higbee came
about four.  Pretty
hemlock tree, arranged
by Maria etc. Lighted about 
five.  Children delighted
Charles has been sick
for a day or two with 
glandular swelling on his 
throat - better.
Wilder went to carry little present to H. B.
Completed

January 2 -
Charlie still unwell
Isaac and I (about eight)
went down to Anna's for
an hour.  Mallie
sent "Hymns of the
Ages".  Elias here most of the day
January 3 - Charlie feeling
badly.  Hattie here in A.M.
Elias to dinner.  Mary Dascomb
about four.
We invited to Mrs. Doolittle's
but did not go on account 
of Charlie.
Completed

January 4 - Sabbath.  Rainy.
Isaac, Mary D. and C. Rich
and Wilder to church in A.M.
I went in P.M. and Isaac at home
with little sick Charlie.
Communion service.  Elias
sat with us Mary Dascomb.
January 5. Monday - Fair.
Anna here in the A.M. Mary D.
here to dinner.  Mallie came
after evening meeting with
Isaac.  Isaac took Mary's
trunk to Dr's and brought
away Mallie.  Mrs. Hill called.
Completed

January 6 Tuesday
Gertrude to meeting in 
morning.  Hattie here. I
went to Dr's an hour in evening
after meeting.  Mallie and Issac
ao meeting.  Mr. Barman called.
Little Charlie better really.
January 7 - Wednesday
Gertrude washing - sweeping
etc. in A. M. Mrs. Ely's gardener
with flowers for Mallie.
Anna here in P.M.
January 8 Thursday -
Charlie not so well. throat
bad.  Mrs. Mussey called
to see Mallie.
Completed

January 9 - Friday -
Mallie and I called at
Jenny's, and I called
at Mrs. McLaughlin's.  Mallie
went to Anna's and called 
at Dr. Strong's and took tea
at Lottie DeWitt's.  To meeting 
and lecture in Evening.  I at home
with Charlie.
January 10 Saturday -
Three Miss Metcalfs and
two Mr. Metcalfs invited to
Mr. Gates.  Isaac and Mallie
went.  Charlie to unwell.
I did not go.  Neither did 
Mother.  I went to Lecture at 8.
Completed

January 11 Sabbath -
I did not go to church in 
A.M.  Mother, Isaac and
Mallie went - I went in 
evening.
January 12 Monday - 
Mallie down to Anna's to 
help make cake etc for
Anna's company tomorrow evening.
January 13 Tuesday
Elias came as we were
at breakfast.
We went to Dr's in evening
Mr. and Mrs. Doolittle, Wilson, Parker,
Ely, Strong, E. W. Metcalf, J. S. Metcalf.
Completed

and Mother.  Nice visit.
January 14 Wednesday
Society at Mrs. Burke's.  Did
not go.  Stormy day.
Thursday  January 15 - Snowy
Mallie and Elias down to Dr's
to dinner.  They with Dr.
anna and Hattie here to tea
and Mary Dascomb.
Charlie we hope better.
Friday January 16 - Snowy
still.  Mallie & Elias
started in the storm - three
hours in the storm.  Three
hours at depot before train came.
Completed

Saturday January 17.  Cold -
Isaac gone to woods took 
some time to get paths.
Libby us here in P.M.
Baby better than for two days past.
Sabbath January 18.  Fine and cold
Mother, Isaac, Charley, Rich 
and Wilder to church in A. M.
I went in evening and heard
Professor Gunning on Geology and Religion.
Monday January 19 washing
sweeping and dusting etc.
Tuesday January 20
Snow.  Mary D. here to dine 
sore throat
Wilder writing to [unclear]
Completed

Wednesday January 31
Mary D. to dinner
Mr. and Mrs. Parker and Mary D to
spend eveing.  almost
sick with cold, sore throat
etc.
Thursday January 22
In bed most of day.
Have headache.
Herbert here.
Friday January 23-
Better.  Isaac went to 
Dr's in evening to meet this
company.  Young people
chiefly.
Completed

Saturday January 24.
Anna came up little 
while.  Piece of her new
dress.  Oyster soup etc.
Sabbath January 25
Fine day.  Still not go out
Capt. Allen's masonic
burial at one P.M.
(1400 looked at his remains)
Monday January 26 - 
snow.  Washing and ironing
a little for Isaac to take 
to Illinois.  Mary D. here
at night.  Talk of President
[unclear]
Completed

Friday January 27
Isaac started for 
Illinois in snow storm
Wilder home from school
for sore throat and cold
Mrs Ely's man with note about
S.S. Program.  Letter from
B. Sprague. 
Wednesday January 28
Children better. 
Letter from Isaac - one
from Mr. Keyes and 
from father at Yarmouth,
Mailed letter to Isaac in [unclear].
Completed

Thursday January 29 -
Fair.  Letter from [unclear]
from Mr. Keyes.  Mrs. Mussey
in P.M. I went down to have
a few minutes - called at Mr. Sanford
on way home for
Atlantic Monthly.  Invitation 
to Mr. Hureberts tomorrow evening.
Friday January 30 - Snowy
Mary D to dinner -
Wrote to Isaac and Letter 
from Isaac and Samuel.
Saturday - January 31 -
Letter from Mr. Keyes with 
check for $100.00
May not so well.
Completed

Sabbath February 1 - 
Charlie Rich to meeting
May lying down all day 
fever and sore throat.  Gertrude
sore throat (her Brooks sick)
Maggie with note from 
Anna.  Dr. up in evening.
Mother up til twelve with
Baby and May etc.  May very 
restless and feverish -
Dover's powder blue pale
Monday February 2 - Fair - 
May better - (oil) -
Mary D. to dinner - 
Letter from Isaac and from 
Elias and Maria.
Mailed letter to Bangor.
Completed

Man came up about hat
stand - will wait till Isaac
comes.
Tuesday February 3 - Cold
Dr. up at noon for signature 
to check.  Mary D. to dinner
Mary feels dull and tire.
Wednesday February 4 - Fair
Gertrude washing.  Her father 
wanted $2.00.  May not so
well.  Mr. Wilbur called
about noon (Charles Rich
got Gaylord Ponce out of the
river.  Where he had gone to
skate alone.) Turkey dinner.
Anna up just after dinner.
Completed

and stayed to supper.  Sent for 
Dr. Strong after school.
He came to see May and left powder.
Thursday February 5 - Snowy
May seems some better -
Still a spot in her throat and
swelled tonsils.  Spots on both
sides.  Don't know what to write 
to Isaac.  Mother did not go
up stairs till two o'clock.  Baby
worried most all the last
half of night.  (Wednesday night.)
Letter from Isaac and from 
Carrie Putnam.
Dr. Strong things May no worse.
Mailed letter to Isaac.
Completed

Friday, February 6 - snow again.
Neither Mother nor I went to 
bed last night.  Gave May
the Ipecac but she still 
breathed badly.  Felt [unclear]
enough.  Baby restless all night.
Letters from Isaac again - all
well.
Waldo cord of weed for 
furnace.  Dr. DeMitt
came up with note, letters etc.
Says (Sh. S. Bonds have 
arrived at Bank for Isaac.
Gertrude sick again.
Completed

Saturday February 7 - 
May had pretty hard 
night.  Dover's Powder.
This morning her nose began
to discharge and we feel 
encouraged - there seemed
a complete dryness and stoppage
before.  Dr. Strong after dinner
Anna all day.
Wrote to Isaac and mailed.
Charles Rich to sleigh ride
Herbert for our horse.  I
said I couldn't [unclear] him.
Completed

Sabbath February 8 - Snowy -
May about the same.  No
worse, perhaps better.  C. Rich
to meeting. Dr. and Anna up
after meeting.  Wilder sic
fever and headache and sore throat
on bed all day.
Hattie up after evening meeting
Stayed all night.
Monday February 9 -
Letter from Isaac and from 
Mallie. Isaac's mailed the 6th
Wilder feels better - Needs
great care constantly.
Anna here in P.M. and all
night.  Dr. DeMittt also a
little while.
May very restless night -
no sleep till 2 o'clock
Completed

Tuesday February 10 -
Felt about sick in morning
but got over it.  May very
comfortable all day.  Anna
here till noon.  Hattie in P.M.
Mrs. Mussey, Miss Grandall
(sent telegram to Isaac)
Mrs. Waldo died.)
Hattie all night.
Wednesday February 11
Dr. DeWitt in morning.  The boys
both  went down to unclear with 
Mr. Waldo early in morning.
Hope May no worse - more 
comfortable night than Monday night.
(Dr. Strong - more oil.)
Completed

Thursday February 12
May seems some better we 
think.  Isaac home about
eleven. Tired.
Dr. DeWitt and Anna both here
in P.M.  Dr. Strong.
Friday February 13.
(Mrs. Nelson died at 
three o'clock this morning.)
Isaac went down and 
brought home the boys.
Grandmother rode a little.
May gaining.
Completed

Thursday February 26 -
Isaac has been sick - for a
week did not have clothes
on.  billious [unclear] fever,
Mr. and Mrs. Highbee called 
yesterday.  Mother is sick, too - got
worn out with care of children.
I went down town to day. bought
Alpaca for dress for self and mother.
Sabbath March 1.
Only Charlie Rich to meeting.
Stormy day.  Children all unwell.
Isaac not well enough to go out.
Completed

Saturday March 7 - Snow
Letter last night from Frances
Putnam and her mother.
Writing to Maria.  Cut
out nankinett waists for
boys.  Mother ripped merino
dress to be washed.  Baby not
very well. May very fretful. 
Children take most of time.
Sabbath March 8 -
I went to I. S. concert in 
P.M.  Isaac and the rest to meeting
in A.M.
- Made drab pants for Isaac this week
Mrs. Simons made coat and vest.
Saturday March 14.
Hattie DeWitt to dinner.
Completed

Sabbath March 15
I went to meeting in  AM
and mother, Isaac and children
Eventide with baby and May.
Monday March 16 -
Isaac started in P.M. to Grafton
on way to Illinois.  Herbert called
just has he left.
Thursday March 17 - Fair
Sweeping, dusting etc.  Then with 
Carrie Mussey to school.  Mrs.
Parkins, Geography and Arithmetic
Miss Smiths spelling - Anna 
here in P.M. Baby not very well
Completed

Wednesday March 18 -
Sweeping parlor - Libbie here 
in A.M. Dr. in P.m.
Mending - Indian Pudding
baked for dinner.
Wrote to Isaac in evening and sent to P. O. 
Thursday March 19 0 
Mother and May to Mrs. Mussey's 
in A.M.
(Traveler for lodging in evening)
Mr. and Mrs. Parker and M. Dascomb
in evening.  Took [unclear] for [unclear] 
Setter from Agricultural [unclear]
Completed

Friday March 20
Anna here in A.M.
Letter from Isaac.
Saturday March 21 Storming
Sabbath March 22 - Fine
I went to church with the
three boys.  Mr. Wlbur preached.
Mr. J. Monteith listened.
Judge Bliss present.  I stopped in
Sunday School. Heard my old class.
Baby not very well - vomited.
Completed

Monday March 23
Letter from Isaac and
draft from Chicago
Hattie up just all night.
Baby vomited in evening and
had convulsions (?) about
ten o'clock
Mr. Waldo in P.M. 
Tuesday March 24 -
Went to bank with $100.00
check, to Dr.  Called at
Anna's. Letter from Isaac
one to little Charlie.
Little boys over  to Jennie's 
and to Anna's.
Completed

Wednesday March 25
snow.  Letter from Isaac
to me and one to Elias for us
to forward.  Mailed it to
night.  Gertrude to meeting.
(Annunciation)
Thursday, March 26-
(Two years since baby George died.)
Cold day.  I wen into secondary school
in A. M. All well.  Mr. Horr's speech.
Anna in P.M.
Letter from George.
Completed

Friday 27 March - Beautiful
Went down at night to go to
Exhibition but came home 
again and Anna with me 
for the [unclear].  Hattie
was up in P.M. Mrs. Mussey 
clan Waldo.
Letter from Isaac.
Saturday 28 March
Snow.
Exhibition in evening.
Sabbath 29 March.  Fair - cold
I went to church in  A. M.
Monday 30 -
Dr., Anna and Libby here just
at night.  Letter from Isaac
Home middle of week
Mrs. [unclear] and [unclear]
Completed

with Model Spider
Tuesday March 31 -
Snow and colder
Letter from Mary Thurston
and from Maria. Pictures
of Edith and Willis and of Mrs.
Ireland, also to mother of 
Hattie Ely.
Wednesday, April 1 -
Fair
Anna up after dinner
Letter from Joseph [unclear]
Completed

Thursday April 2
Not very well -
Anna up in P.M.
I went to Evening meeting
with Charles Rich.
Friday April 3
Isaac home just at 
tea time.  Down town in 
Evening to Political Meeting.
Saturday April 4 -
Anna here.
Not feeling well tooth
and head ache - catarrh
Isaac down town 
Various callers. Amanda Sondfen.
Completed

Sabbath April 5
I went to evening meeting
Monday April 6 - Stormy
Isaac down town - Election.
Tuesday April 7
Sabbath April 12
To meeting in evening
Sabbath April 19
meeting in evening
Sabbath April 26
Baby nine months old
Meeting in evening ' - "Give us
this day our daily bread."
Completed

Monday 27
Down town with old
Neopolitan bonnet to be repaired
Tuesday 28 
Dr. and Anna and 
Aunt Naomi and Miss D. here
to tea.
Wednesday 29
Isaac gone most of day
house cleaning up stairs.
Thursday 30 -
National Fast - went to
meeting.  Herbert - Mr. Jenkins
all think Mr. Wilbur's sermon
should be printed
Completed

May 1
May four years old.  Went
to school with Flora and Charley in
the morning.
I want my cup reaping full - heavy
Charlie - vomiting is good for me.
Libby up July 6 Monday night about work
I went down Tuesday morning found
Mary Highbee - all doing well
rain, heavy showers.
Completed

Charles wants to know if David
was a Buckeye or a Yankee
That little man that killed 
the big giant.
May I want to do something
that's worth something.
I wish the days would just run
bak a few little days and begin
over again so as to have
years again (Charlie)
I like Aunt Mollie. She is so
pretty
- 'Knock and it shall be opened unto
you, and here I stand knocking."
Mother, where is that little flower?
I can't find it. I do not know,
I said. Well I guess it died
and went to heaven.  May.
Is Jesus taller than a camel or
and elephant? (Charlie)
